《'''在永恒之門'''》（Op de drempel van de eeuwigheid），或稱《'''悲痛的老人'''》是一幅[[梵高|梵高]]1890年5月初在[[聖雷米|聖雷米]]精神病院完成的油畫，<ref name="Letter 288">{{cite web|title=To Theo van Gogh. The Hague, Sunday, 26 and Monday, 27 November 1882|url=http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let288/letter.html|work=Vincent van Gogh: The Letters|publisher=''[[Van_Gogh_Museum|Van Gogh Museum]]''|accessdate=2015-11-14|archive-date=2016-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160929182358/http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let288/letter.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Hulsker|first=Jan|title=The Complete Van Gogh: Paintings, Drawings, Sketches|year=1986|publisher=''[[Random_House|Random House]]''|isbn=0-517-44867-X|page=444}}</ref> 此畫基於其1882年在[[海牙|海牙]]繪成的鉛筆草稿完成，畫中人物是一名名叫“Adrianus Jacobus Zuyderland”老兵。<ref name= "Letter 172">{{cite web|title=To Theo van Gogh. Etten, mid-September 1881|url=http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let172/letter.html|work=Vincent van Gogh: The Letters|publisher=''[[Van_Gogh_Museum|Van Gogh Museum]]''|accessdate=2015-11-14|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304054055/http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let172/letter.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 而原畫的靈感來源則是[[休伯特·冯·赫科默|休伯特·冯·赫科默]]繪製的畫作《切爾西醫院的星期日》。<ref>{{cite web |last=von Herkomer |first=Hubert |title=THe Last Muster |url=http://www.liverpoolmuseums.org.uk/ladylever/collections/thelastmuster.asp |publisher=[[Lady_Lever_Art_Gallery|Lady Lever Art Gallery]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423225329/http://www.liverpoolmuseums.org.uk/ladylever/collections/thelastmuster.asp |archivedate=2012-04-23 |accessdate=2015-11-14 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Korda|first=Andrea|title=The Streets as Art Galleries: Hubert Herkomer, William Powell Frith, and the Artistic Advertisement|url=http://www.19thc-artworldwide.org/index.php/spring12/korda-on-the-streets-as-art-galleries-hubert-herkomer-william-powell-frith-and-the-artistic-advertisement|publisher=Nineteenth-Century Art Worldwide|accessdate=2015-11-14|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304104712/http://www.19thc-artworldwide.org/index.php/spring12/korda-on-the-streets-as-art-galleries-hubert-herkomer-william-powell-frith-and-the-artistic-advertisement|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Naifeh & White Smith">{{cite book|title=Van Gogh: The Life|year=2011|publisher=[[Random_House|Random House]]|first1=Steven|last1=Naifeh|first2=Gregory|last2=White Smith|isbn=0-375-50748-5|url=http://www.randomhouse.com/book/119583/van-gogh-by-steven-naifeh-and-gregory-white-smith|page=318|access-date=2015-11-14|archive-date=2014-12-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226011143/http://www.randomhouse.com/book/119583/van-gogh-by-steven-naifeh-and-gregory-white-smith|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Notes 233|url=http://www.vangoghbiography.com/notes.php?valuesearch=313|work=Van Gogh: The Life|publisher=VanGoghBiography.com|accessdate=2015-11-14|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305030932/http://www.vangoghbiography.com/notes.php?valuesearch=313|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

畫中的老兵坐在爐火旁，雙手掩面。這可能也表現出了畫家創作時的悲痛心情及畫家對神與永恒的信仰，而這些事物的難以感知實際也是其悲痛的來源，這一點在其早年的書信中就可以看出<ref name= "Letter 294">{{cite web|title= Letter 294: To Theo van Gogh. The Hague, between about Wednesday, 13 and about Monday, 18 December 1882|url= http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let294/letter.html|work= Vincent van Gogh: The Letters|publisher= [[Van_Gogh_Museum|Van Gogh Museum]]|at= Note 4|quote= |accessdate= |archive-date= 2018-12-07|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20181207015624/http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let294/letter.html|dead-url= no}}</ref><ref>Hulsker (1980) p. 69</ref><ref>Erickson (1998) [http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Sz0Pla9mLSYC&pg=PA77&lpg=PA77&dq=van+gogh+%22while+van+gogh+sought+a+meaningful+experience+of+faith&source=bl&ots=LhAT2MuhuV&sig=w2dnxIN3fcEtWDUIej_mrHXjPCI&hl=en&sa=X&ei=-JloT-G6G5P04QT1-NzuCA&sqi=2&ved=0CCAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=van%20gogh%20%22while%20van%20gogh%20sought%20a%20meaningful%20experience%20of%20faith&f=false p. 77]</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Erickson|first=Kathleen Powers|title=At Eternity's Gate: The Spiritual Vision of Vincent Van Goh|url=http://books.google.lu/books?id=Sz0Pla9mLSYC&pg=PA86&lpg=PA86&dq=Belief+in+a+%22life+beyond+the+grave%22+is+central+to+one+of+van+Gogh%27s+first+accomplished+lithographs&source=bl&ots=LhAV5QwjwV&sig=iEZ1a5kcoaZjGQjxL6gpj9caiDE&hl=de&sa=X&ei=RFeMT4GEM5H0sgaO__jXCw&ved=0CB0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Belief%20in%20a%20%22life%20beyond%20the%20grave%22%20is%20central%20to%20one%20of%20van%20Gogh%27s%20first%20accomplished%20lithographs&f=false|publisher=[[Google_books|Google books]]|access-date=2015-11-14|archive-date=2012-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120103104/http://books.google.lu/books?id=Sz0Pla9mLSYC&pg=PA86&lpg=PA86&dq=Belief+in+a+%22life+beyond+the+grave%22+is+central+to+one+of+van+Gogh%27s+first+accomplished+lithographs&source=bl&ots=LhAV5QwjwV&sig=iEZ1a5kcoaZjGQjxL6gpj9caiDE&hl=de&sa=X&ei=RFeMT4GEM5H0sgaO__jXCw&ved=0CB0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Belief%20in%20a%20%22life%20beyond%20the%20grave%22%20is%20central%20to%20one%20of%20van%20Gogh%27s%20first%20accomplished%20lithographs&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==創作過程==
1882年11月24日梵高在給弟弟的信中說：<ref name= "Letter 286">{{cite web|title=To Theo van Gogh. The Hague, Friday, 24 November 1882|url=http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let286/letter.html|work=Vincent van Gogh: The Letters|publisher=''[[Van_Gogh_Museum|Van Gogh Museum]]''|accessdate=2018-01-08|archive-date=2018-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180325134035/http://vangoghletters.org/vg/letters/let286/letter.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{Quote|text=這倆天我畫了兩幅老人像，畫上的老人兩隻胳膊拄著膝蓋，臉埋在手裡...我想下次畫得更好一些。我可能還會印一張出來。這幅畫很好地描繪了一個穿著打了補丁的[[邦巴津|邦巴津]]大衣的禿頂老人。}}

幾天後梵高就把行動付諸實施：<ref name="Letter 288"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Notes 341, 342|url=http://vangoghbiography.com/notes.php?valuesearch=318|work=Van Gogh: The Life|publisher=VanGoghBiography.com|accessdate=2018-01-08|archive-date=2019-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190929183802/http://vangoghbiography.com/notes.php?valuesearch=318|dead-url=no}}</ref> {{Quote|text=我覺得畫家應該通過作品表達他的觀點。我試圖通過印刷品來達到這一目的——但是好像不太成功。它沒有現實那般美麗而驚人，相比而言這只是一個模糊的鏡像，而現實，就好像[[讓-弗朗索瓦·米勒|米勒]]所相信的那樣，昭示著冥冥之中有神靈或永恆的存在。那老人安靜地坐在火爐旁的角落里，甚至都不一定知道這一切...這不是什麼神學——就算是最窮的樵夫或礦工也總有那麼一剎那感覺到永恆之門的存在}}

